#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn6.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Devadattasutta "
msgstr "12. About Devadatta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.154, sc1
msgctxt "sn6.12:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn6.12:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.12:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the beautiful Brahmā Sahampati, lighting up the entire Vulture’s Peak, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "

msgctxt "sn6.12:1.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho brahmā sahampati devadattaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.333, sc2
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.1"
msgid "“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti, "
msgstr "“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ; "
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti, "
msgstr "Honor destroys a sinner, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti. "
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
